description: Sun Peak Metals Corp., a junior mining company, engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of resource properties for the mining of precious and base metals. It primarily explores for gold and copper deposits. The company holds interests in the Shire project that comprises four exploration licenses, including Nefasit, Adi Dairo, Terer, and Meli covering an area of approximately 900 square kilometers located in northern Ethiopia. Sun Peak Metals Corp. was incorporated in 2016 and is headquartered in White Rock, Canada.
